  "prompt": "Which is best mobile under 15000?",
  "response": "As of the latest information available, several smartphones under INR 15,000 offer excellent features and performance. Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 30**:\n   - Display: 6.5-inch Full HD+ screen\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G95\n   - RAM/Storage: 4GB/6GB RAM, 64GB/128GB storage\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 30W fast charging\n   - Camera: 48MP triple camera setup\n\n2. **Xiaomi Redmi Note 10**:\n   - Display: 6.43-inch Full HD+ AMOLED display\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 678\n   - RAM/Storage: 4GB/6GB RAM, 64GB/128GB storage\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - Camera: 48MP quad-camera setup\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M32**:\n   - Display: 6.4-inch Full HD+ Super AMOLED screen\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G80\n   - RAM/Storage: 4GB/6GB RAM, 64GB/128GB storage\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 15W fast charging\n   - Camera: 64MP quad-camera setup\n\n4. **Poco M3**:\n   - Display: 6.53-inch Full HD+ screen\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 662\n   - RAM/Storage: 6GB RAM, 64GB/128GB storage\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 18W fast charging\n   - Camera: 48MP triple camera setup\n\n5. **Motorola Moto G40 Fusion**:\n   - Display: 6.8-inch Full HD+ screen with 120Hz refresh rate\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 732G\n   - RAM/Storage: 4GB/6GB RAM, 64GB/128GB storage\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 20W fast charging\n   - Camera: 64MP triple camera setup\n\nWhen choosing the best phone for you, consider what features are most important, like camera quality, battery life, or display type. Additionally, prices and availability can change, so it is a good idea to check the latest reviews and prices before making a purchase.",
